: 2\nExplanation: The optimal substring here is \"bc\".\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: s = \"cbzxy\"\nOutput: -1\nExplanation: There are no characters that appear twice in s.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= s.length <= 300`\n\n- `s` contains only lowercase English letters.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/largest-substring-between-two-equal-characters/","problemName":"Largest Substring Between Two Equal Characters","problemNumber":1624,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given a string `s`, return *the length of the longest substring between two equal characters, excluding the two characters.* If there is no such substring return `-1`.\n\nA **substring** is a contiguous sequence of characters within a string.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: s = \"aa\"\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: The optimal substring here is an empty substring between the two 'a's.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: s = \"abca\"\nOutput: 2\nExplanation: The optimal substring here is \"bc\".","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: s = \"cbzxy\"\nOutput: -1\nExplanation: There are no characters that appear twice in s.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= s.length <= 300`\n\n- `s` contains only lowercase English letters.","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Easy","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"Given a string `s`, return *the length of the longest substring between two equal characters, excluding the two characters.* If there is no such substring return `-1`.\n\nA **substring** is a contiguous sequence of characters within a string.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: s = \"aa\"\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: The optimal substring here is an empty substring between the two 'a's.\