espond to the operators `'+'` (addition), `'-'` (subtraction), `'*'` (multiplication), and `'/'` (division).\n\nIt's guaranteed that no subtree will yield a value that exceeds `10⁹` in absolute value, and all the operations are valid (i.e., no division by zero).\n\n**Follow up:** Could you design the expression tree such that it is more modular? For example, is your design able to support additional operators without making changes to your existing `evaluate` implementation?\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1628-design-an-expression-tree-with-evaluate-function/1628-untitled-diagram.png]]\n\nInput: s = [\"3\",\"4\",\"+\",\"2\",\"*\",\"7\",\"/\"]\nOutput: 2\nExplanation: this expression evaluates to the above binary tree with expression ((3+4)*2)/7) = 14/7 = 2.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1628-design-an-expression-tree-with-evaluate-function/1628-untitled-diagram2.png]]\n\nInput: s = [\"4\",\"5\",\"2\",\"7\",\"+\",\"-\",\"*\"]\nOutput: -16\nExplanation: this expression evaluates to the above binary tree with expression 4*(5-(2+7)) = 4*(-4) = -16.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= s.length < 100`\n\n- `s.length` is odd.\n\n- `s` consists of numbers and the characters `'+'`, `'-'`, `'*'`, and `'/'`.\n\n- If `s[i]` is a number, its integer representation is no more than `10⁵`.\n\n- It is guaranteed that `s` is a valid expression.\n\n- The absolute value of the result and intermediate values will not exceed `10⁹`.\n\n- It is guaranteed that no expression will include division by zero.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/design-an-expression-tree-with-evaluate-function/","problemName":"Design an Expression Tree With Evaluate Function","problemNumber":1628,"problemSlug":"design-an-expression-tree-with-evaluate-function","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1628,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","String"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"A newly designed keypad was 