nomial must be in **strictly** descending order by its `power` value. Also, terms with a `coefficient` of `0` are omitted.\n\nGiven two polynomial linked list heads, `poly1` and `poly2`, add the polynomials together and return *the head of the sum of the polynomials*.\n\n**`PolyNode` format:**\n\nThe input/output format is as a list of `n` nodes, where each node is represented as its `[coefficient, power]`. For example, the polynomial `5x³ + 4x - 7` would be represented as: `[[5,3],[4,1],[-7,0]]`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1634-add-two-polynomials-represented-as-linked-lists/1634-ex1.png","sequence":3,"sha256":"f3c0a1b50070cffe91795771ba98ae5c77da85a8bc3d98639580a6204d40436c","type":"image"},{"sequence":4,"text":"Input: poly1 = [[1,1]], poly2 = [[1,0]]\n\nOutput: [[1,1],[1,0]]\n\nExplanation: poly1 = x. poly2 = 1. The sum is x + 1.","type":"code"},{"sequence":5,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":6,"text":"Input: poly1 = [[2,2],[4,1],[3,0]], poly2 = [[3,2],[-4,1],[-1,0]]\n\nOutput: [[5,2],[2,0]]\n\nExplanation: poly1 = 2x2 + 4x + 3. poly2 = 3x2 - 4x - 1. The sum is 5x2 + 2. Notice that we omit the \"0x\" term.","type":"code"},{"sequence":7,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":8,"text":"Input: poly1 = [[1,2]], poly2 = [[-1,2]]\n\nOutput: []\n\nExplanation: The sum is 0. We return an empty list.","type":"code"},{"sequence":9,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `0 <= n <= 10⁴`\n\n- `-10⁹ <= PolyNode.coefficient <= 10⁹`\n\n- `PolyNode.coefficient != 0`\n\n- `0 <= PolyNode.power <= 10⁹`\n\n- `PolyNode.power > PolyNode.next.power`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Linked List","Math","Two Pointers"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"A polynomial linked list is a special type of linked list where every node represents a term in a polynomial expression.\n\nEach node has three attributes:\n\n- `coefficient`: an integer representing the number multiplier of the term. The coefficient of the term `**9**x⁴` is `9`.\n\n- `power`: an integer representing the exponent. The power of the term `9x**⁴**` is `4`.\n\n- `next`: a pointer to the next node in the list, or `null` if it is the last node of the list.\n\nFor example, the polynomial `5x³ + 4x - 7` is represented by the polynomial linked list illustrated below:\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1634-add-two-polynomials-represented-as-linked-lists/1634-polynomial2.png]]\n\nThe polynomial linked list must be in its standard form: the polynomial must be in **strictly** descending order by its `power` value. Also, terms with a `coefficient` of `0` are omitted.\n\nGiven two polynomial linked list heads, `poly1` and `poly2`, add the polynomials together and return *the head of the sum of the polynomials*.\n\n**`PolyNode` format:**\n\nThe input/output format is as a list of `n` nodes, where each node is represented as its `[coefficient, power]`. For example, the polynomial `5x³ + 4x - 7` would be represented as: `[[5,3],[4,1],[-7,0]]`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1634-add-two-polynomials-represented-as-linked-lists/1634-ex1.png]]\n\nInput: poly1 = [[1,1]], poly2 = [[1,0]]\n\nOutput: [[1,1],[1,0]]\n\nExplanation: poly1 = x. poly2 = 1. The sum is x + 1.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: poly1 = [[2,2],[4,1],[3,0]], poly2 = [[3,2],[-4,1],[-1,0]]\n\nOutput: [[5,2],[2,0]]\n\nExplanation: poly1 = 2x2 + 4x + 3. poly2 = 3x2 - 4x - 1. The sum is 5x2 + 2. Notice that we omit the \"0x\" term.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: poly1 = [[1,2]], poly2 = [[-1,2]]\n\nOutput: []\n\nExplanation: The sum is 0. We return an empty list.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `0 <= n <= 10⁴`\n\n- `-10⁹ <= PolyNode.coefficient <= 10⁹`\n\n- `PolyNode.coefficient != 0`\n\n- `0 <= PolyNode.power <= 10⁹`\n\n- `PolyNode.power > PolyNode.next.power`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/add-two-polynomial